---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Retaining Walls Officer VIC | Sleeper, Block & Concrete | Free Quote"
  description="Specialist retaining wall builders in Officer VIC. Sloping blocks in Officer Hills, Arcadia & Aspect estates need engineered walls. Free fixed-price quotes — call (03) 9003 0223."
  canonical="https://pakenhamretainingwalls.com.au/officer/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Officer VIC 3809</span>
      <h1>Retaining walls for <span class="accent">Officer&rsquo;s</span> sloping blocks.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Officer&rsquo;s newer estates &mdash; Arcadia, Aspect, Riverbank &mdash; were built into a slope.
        Almost every block needs at least one retaining wall. We build them right the first time.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Officer specifics</span>
      <h2>Why Officer blocks usually need engineered walls.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 60rem;">
        <p>
          Officer sits on the western edge of the Cardinia Shire, between Beaconsfield and
          Pakenham. The land here is genuinely sloped &mdash; the new estates were terraced
          rather than levelled, which means most blocks have a 1&ndash;3 metre fall from front
          to back, or one side to the other.
        </p>
        <p>
          That fall has to be retained somewhere. Either the developer did it
          (front of the block, common in Arcadia) or the homeowner has to do it (rear or
          side fence line, very common in Aspect and Riverbank). The walls left for the
          homeowner are the ones we build.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Common Officer retaining wall scenarios</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rear yard cut-and-fill walls</strong> &mdash; usually 0.6&ndash;1.5m, often crossing the fence line. Requires neighbour notification under the Fences Act.</li>
          <li><strong>Side-boundary tiered walls</strong> &mdash; two or three short walls stepping down a slope, far stronger than a single tall wall.</li>
          <li><strong>Driveway retaining</strong> &mdash; supporting a sloped driveway against the house pad.</li>
          <li><strong>Pool surround walls</strong> &mdash; many Officer pools are partially in-ground because of the slope, which means short walls all around.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What Officer estates have in common</h3>
        <p>
          Reactive clay subsoil and developer-imported fill on top. The fill is often poorly
          compacted and holds water. A retaining wall built into this without proper drainage
          and footing depth will lean within 5&ndash;10 years. We dig past the fill, footing
          into the clay, and run an ag-pipe to a legal stormwater point on every job.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Wall types we build in Officer.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/timber-retaining-walls/"><h3>Timber sleeper</h3><p>Most economical, 15&ndash;40 year lifespan.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/concrete-sleeper-walls/"><h3>Concrete sleeper</h3><p>50+ year lifespan, ideal for taller walls.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/block-retaining-walls/"><h3>Block / masonry</h3><p>Premium look, long lifespan.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/excavation-earthworks/"><h3>Earthworks</h3><p>Cut-and-fill, drainage, levelling.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Officer site visit &mdash; free.</h2>
        <p>Book a free measure-up and fixed-price quote.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Quote online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
